<section sectnbr = "5E">
<servcat sctnbr = "05" scnbr = "05">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENBP70A5506004" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
TCM Removal and Installation
</title>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
As the TCM consists of precision parts, the TCM will be damaged if it is exposed to an excessively large impact.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Handle the TCM carefully so as not to impact it.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Since the slope sensor has been removed together with TCM, be sure to perform 
<intxref refid = "AENBP70A5506042">Slope Sensor Calibration</intxref>
. If it is not performed, some controls, including neutral idle control, could not function correctly.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
When the TCM is replaced, be sure to perform 
<intxref refid = "AENBP70A5506001">TCM Learning Value Initialization</intxref>
. If it is not performed, the result could be greater gear shift shock.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A5506004001">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect negative (–) cable at battery.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disable air bag system. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A8206001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove glove box. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect connector (2) from slope sensor (1).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect connectors (4) from TCM (3).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove TCM with slope sensor by removing nuts (5).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove TCM from its bracket (6). 
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A550045.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "57.986mm" ver = "03" gw = "239" gh = "148"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A5506004002">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
Reverse removal procedure noting the following points.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Tighten each nut (1) and bolt (2) to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T5E003">
<t-part>
Bracket nut
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
14
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
1.4
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
10.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
<torqueitem id = "T5E004">
<t-part>
TCM bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
b
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
4.9
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
0.50
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
4.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A550046.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "57.957mm" ver = "01" gw = "242" gh = "148"/>
</figure>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Perform 
<intxref refid = "AENBP70A5506042">Slope Sensor Calibration</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
After replacing TCM, perform 
<intxref refid = "AENBP70A5506001">TCM Learning Value Initialization</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Enable air bag system after TCM is back in place. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A8206002"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
